oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Factors Associated with Colostral Hydrometer Values
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Maunsell, Fiona
Morin, Dawn
Constable, Peter
McCoy, Gene
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: hydrometer reading
breed
lactation number
milk
fat
protein
first milking colostrum
dry period length
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The aims of this study were 1) to determine if unadjusted hydrometer readings were associated with breed, lactation number, or season of calving, and 2) to determine if the hydrometer readings were correlated with 305 day yields of milk, fat, or protein for the preceding or subsequent lactation, weight of first milking colostrum, or dry period length.
